    "body": "Hi @jrusselg I've been testing deploying these contracts with besu.\r\n\r\nI used https://github.com/ConsenSys/UniversalToken as the ERC1400 implementation.\r\n\r\nI can confirm that the solidity contract code needs to be compiled against the `istanbul` or later evm version in order to get the opcode support.\r\n\r\nOn most recent versions of besu, setting any of `istanbulBlock`, `muirGlacierBlock`, or `berlinBlock` in the genesis should work with a free gas network (you may need to match the compiled evm version of the contract with the hard fork).\r\n \r\nIf you want to use any later hard forks with a free gas network: `londonBlock`, `arrowGlacierBlock` or `grayGlacierBlock` (none of which are required for private networks), then you need a fix that has just been released in https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/releases/tag/22.7.0-RC1\r\n\r\nIn addition, you'll need to set to `baseFeePerGas` to zero in the genesis, like so:\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"config\": {\r\n    ...\r\n    \"arrowGlacierBlock\": 0,\r\n    ...\r\n  },\r\n  \"baseFeePerGas\": \"0x0\",\r\n  \"nonce\": \"0x0\",\r\n  ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nClosing this issue. Please reopen if you experience further problems with this.\r\n",
